definitions.definition: An enclosed underground space, often under a building , used for storage or shelter .
examples: The farmhouse has several additions, added over many decades; it has three cellars , and one of them is older than the other two.

definitions.definition: A wine collection , especially when stored in a cellar.
examples: The insurance company valued his cellar at $27,000, largely on the strength of his bottles of 1972 Château Hypothetica.

definitions.definition: ( slang ) Last place in a league or competition ; some rank near last place.
examples: The Tigers have been in the cellar all year long, and I'm tired of it.
Most of my tools and hardware are in the garage, but I keep some tools in the cellar , too, mainly for convenience.
